<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:lime;">&quot;The Sassy Roguette&quot; (Hydra)</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=annabriespiritsoaring@thesaryrntavern>Annabriespiritsoaring</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(12/5/03 7:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5598.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> LDoN does have raids...</span><hr size=1> After people are able to gear up in LDoN, it would be possible to start LDoN raids...people would be able to organize fairly easily a LDoN raid in a LDoN focused guild. <br>
<br>
Casual LDoN raids would be a nice change of pace from LDon grinding. Also its important to understand that people in the guild would do other things, not JUST LDon. I am sure many members would go off and do some planar XP and AA mining when they are the correct levels. I am not planing on some militia mentality guild that will break fingers of anyone who isn't in a LDoN. <br>
<br>
The idea is to put together a guild of like minded people who want to do mainly LDoN groups, eventually working into LDoN raids, if people find that interesting. Many people I know, including myself, dislike raiding, and find it boring and time consuming. I see many problems in the bigger guilds no matter what their loot distribution system is, many people feel as though they are being looked over, or that they are being screwed out of loot. an LDoN focused guild would have less problems with such an arrangement, as the main loot in LDoN is point bought, not dropped. (Though we all know, no matter what system is being used, somebody is gonna feel like they are being screwed, thats just the way it goes. People have feelings, and sometimes they aren't justified.)<br>
<br>
and honestly, this guild just isn't for everyone, some people are going to think the idea sucks, and they are perfectly justified in their feelings, as it would suck for them. Though I am just trying to see if there would be a large enough interest in the idea, if so then Saryrn would have an alternative to huge raiding guilds. A huge LDoN guild to find LDoN groups quickly and easily. Eventually most people would find a group or two of people they enjoy playing with, and there would develop &quot;clicks&quot; of players. Thats good in some ways, not so good in others, but thats the way social structures work. <br>
<br>
Anyways, I will keep checking back on further comments, all the input I get is useful. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=annabriespiritsoaring@thesaryrntavern>Annabriespiritsoaring</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(12/6/03 12:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5598.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tenkei is now re-forming, as saryrns LDoN guild...</span><hr size=1> If your tired of having a hard time finding LDoN groups, or aren't finding them fast enough, then Tenkei has your solution. We are building our player base around the idea of LDoN players level 20-65 can find groups faster in a guild that focuses on doing LDoN. Like minded people joining together to get the most out of LDoN.<br>
<br>
